parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or experience erratic behavior, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The windshield wipers
headlights
and instrument panel lights turn on and off randomly
the horn sounds intermittently
the speedometer and tachometer needles move erratically
and the vehicle stalls or loses power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
and the vehicle stalls or loses power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbag to deploy unexpectedly or fail to deploy in the event of a crash, which can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag indicator light illuminates
the airbag deploys unexpectedly
and the vehicle experiences electrical system failures that can affect the airbag system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door and window systems can cause the doors to lock up or fail, leading to safety concerns and inconvenience.
symptoms: The sliding doors lock up or fail
the windows do not operate properly
and the door electrical harnesses malfunction or short circuit.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition and starting systems can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to inconvenience and safety concerns.
symptoms: The ignition switch fails
the vehicle hesitates to start
and the vehicle stalls or loses power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake wear and failure can lead to reduced stopping power, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: Squealing or grinding noises when braking
vibration when braking
strong burning smell
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pads worn down to metal
warped rotors.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corroded and Faulty Tire Valve Stems
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corroded and faulty tire valve stems can cause sudden tire deflation, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The TPMS warning light illuminates
tire pressure drops suddenly
valve stem breaks off
and air escapes rapidly from the tire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TPMS can lead to underinflated tires, which can cause accidents, blowouts, and loss of control, resulting in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The TPMS warning light illuminates
tire pressure drops suddenly
and the system fails to alert the driver of low tire pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.
